    The FilterApplication class provides functionalities for managing and applying filters to images.

    Represents a single link in a chain of filters to be applied sequentially to an image.

    Represents a filter command that can be executed on an image.

    Factory class for managing and providing filter commands in the application.

    Manages a chain of filters applied to an image.

    Interface for handling image pixel format conversions.

    The ImageApplication class provides functionalities for managing image-related operations in the application.
    ImageBuilder
    Builder class for creating and configuring instances of images.
    ImageBuilderInterface
    Interface defining the basic properties needed to build an image.
    ImageBusiness
    Represents an image with pixel data, file path, and format information.
    ImageDataAccess
    Interface defining the operations for accessing image data.
    NegativeCommand
     
    PBMDataAccess
    Provides functionality to read and write PBM image files in both ASCII (P1) and binary (P4) formats.
    PGMDataAccess
    Provides functionality to read and write PPM image files in both ASCII (P2) and binary (P5) formats.
    PNGDataAccess
    Provides functionality to read and write PNG image files.
    PNMDataAccess
    Abstract base class for handling PNM (Portable AnyMap) image formats.
    PNMDataAccess.RowGenerator
    Functional interface for generating rows of pixel data.
    PNMWithMaxValueDataAccess
    Abstract base class for handling PNM image formats that include a "max value" field in their headers.
    PPMDataAccess
    Provides functionality to read and write PPM image files in both ASCII (P3) and binary (P6) formats.
    PreferencesApplication
    Provides a high-level interface for managing user preferences in the application.
    PreferencesBusiness
    Provides business logic for managing user preferences in the application.
    PreferencesBusinessInterface
    Defines the behavior that a generic preferences model should expose to the application controller.
    PreferencesDataAccess
    Provides access to user preferences, including loading, saving, and creating default preferences.
    PreferencesDataAccessInterface
    Interface defining the contract between data access operations and business for managing user preferences.

    RotateRightCommand

    StateApplication
    Provides an application-level implementation of editor state management.
    StateChangeEvent
    Represents an application event that allows the registration and removal of listeners for state changes.

    Interface for listening to state changes in the editor.
    ThreeChannel
     
    TranslationBusiness
    Provides the business logic for managing translations in the application.
    TranslationsApplication
    Provides an application-level interface for managing translations and language settings.

    TranslationsDataAccess
    Provides access to translations and supported languages for both backend and frontend modules.
    TranslationsDataAccessInterface
    Defines the behavior that a generic translations data access object should expose to the business logic.
